  "summary": "A compact ritual-innovation booklet offering seven complete additions: Miriam's fish, leeks, beets, orange segments, Maxwell House coffee, turnip peels, and Miriam's Cup. Each addition has a specific insertion point and internal explanation, making this source unusually easy to preserve as coherent units, though food safety, consent, trauma context, and one violent Psalm sequence require clear gates.",
  "sourceAssessment": {
    "voice": "Learned, playful, text-rich, and inventive, pairing historical Jewish sources with concrete objects and explicit placement instructions.",
    "bestUses": [
      "Optional Seder-plate personalization",
      "Feminist, LGBTQ, environmental, traditional, and playful theme paths",
      "Host-guide explanations of why an added object is present",
      "Longer participatory Seders that can hold one complete ritual innovation"
    ],
    "beginnerRisks": [
      "The additions are optional and must not be mistaken for universally traditional Seder-plate requirements.",
      "Fish, nuts, horseradish, beets, leeks, coffee, and other foods require allergy, dietary, and child-safety alternatives.",
      "Some Talmudic and biblical passages are quoted without basic background that a first-time guest will need.",
      "The turnip reading invokes Bergen-Belsen and must be trauma-sensitive; the following anger Psalms must not be appended."
    ],
    "politicalContext": "The source focuses on ritual inclusion rather than contemporary Israel-Palestine advocacy. Preserve its inclusive orange story and Miriam-centered readings. Exclude the collective-destruction verses in the turnip section under the project's peace-focused policy, while retaining the survivor story and hopeful context that precede them.",
    "creditContext": "Credit Isaac Gantwerk Mayer and A Second Passover Seder Plate with Seven Additions on the final sources page. Keep each object with its complete explanation, preserve embedded Ritualwell, Joan Nathan, New York Times, biblical, and rabbinic attributions, and indicate any changes under the ShareAlike terms."
  },
